river.py` of a logger being instantiated to the root logger unless another logger is specifically provided like\r\n\r\n```python\r\n        if logger is None:\r\n            logger = logging.getLogger()\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnother logger is never explicitly provided and as such thousands of records are submitted to the root logger. This becomes a problem when using black from another python script.\r\n\r\nPerhaps a more elegant solution would be to retrieve a named logger like \r\n\r\n```python\r\n# driver.py\r\n        if logger is None:\r\n            logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\r\n```\r\n\r\nthat can then be configured like\r\n\r\n```python\r\n# main.py\r\nlogging.getLogger('blib2to3.pgen2.driver').setLevel(logging.WARNING)\r\n```\r\n\r\nWould a pull request addressing this be considered?\r\n\r\nOperating system: MacOS 10.14.3\r\nPython version: 3.7.2\r\n*Black* version: 18.9b0\r\nDoes also happen on master: Probably","closed_by":{"login":"ambv","id":55281,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU1Mjgx","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/55281?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/ambv","html_url":"https://github.com/ambv","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ambv/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ambv/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ambv/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ambv/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ambv/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ambv/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ambv/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ambv/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ambv/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/psf/black/issues/715/reactions","total_count":2,"+1":2,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0